Running the maven example
=========================

Before running the maven examples, you must install TestBench into your local maven repository by
executing the following command in the <TESTBENCH PACKAGE ROOT>/maven directory:

	mvn install:install-file \
	-Dfile=vaadin-testbench-3.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar \
	-Djavadoc=vaadin-testbench-3.0.0-SNAPSHOT-javadoc.jar \
	-DpomFile=pom.xml


About the maven example project
===============================

How the project was created
---------------------------
The project was created using the vaadin-archetype-clean archetype. E.g.

	mvn archetype:generate \
	-DarchetypeGroupId=com.vaadin \
	-DarchetypeArtifactId=vaadin-archetype-clean \
	-DarchetypeVersion=LATEST \
	-DgroupId=your.company \
	-DartifactId=project-name \
	-Dversion=1.0 \
	-Dpackaging=war

After the project was generated, the pom.xml was edited and the following dependency added:
    <dependency>
      <groupId>com.vaadin</groupId>
      <artifactId>vaadin-testbench</artifactId>
      <version>3.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    </dependency>

That's it.


Screen shot comparison in the example project
---------------------------------------------
Screen shot comparison is a feature of TestBench. In the example project the screen shot reference
images are placed in src/test/resources/screenshots/reference/ and error reports are stored in
target/testbench/errors/

See src/test/java/com/vaadin/testbenchexample/TestBenchExample.java for the code that sets the parameters
that specify the above directories.